{
  "texts": [
    "The government was put in an awkward corner because, Charles Elliot, their representative in China mishandled the situation.",
    "He convinced the drug smugglers to give him their drugs in return for British IOUs, and then he handed over the drugs to the Chinese authorities for destruction.",
    "When Parliament discovered that they could not afford to make good on the IOUs, they thought they could use force to get the Chinese to pay the 2 million pounds for the lost opium.",
    "Here is the question that I gave to the students:",
    "What were the Opium Wars? 2."
  ]
}